import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='values', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['values'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['values'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['values'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['values'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.barplot(x=["width", "height"], y=[data["width"].mean(), data["height"].mean()], palette="Blues_d")
    ax.axhline(data["height"].mean(), color="red", linestyle="--", label=f"Height Mean: {data['height'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axhline(data["width"].mean(), color="green", linestyle="--", label=f"Width Mean: {data['width'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.set_title("What is the average width and height of the dataset?")
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['values'], ax=ax, color='skyblue')
    ax.axvline(data['values'].min(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Min: {data['values'].min():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['values'].max(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data['values'].max():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['values'].median(), color='orange', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['values'].median():.2f}")
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    plt.title('What is the range of values in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data['month_year'] = data['date'].dt.to_period('M')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='month_year', y='values', data=data, ci=None)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    chart.axhline(y=data['values'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('Are there any patterns or trends in the values over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
